commit.message:
New setup.py, codecov.io, shields.io.

Normalizing across all of my projects.

Fixing coverage.

Looks like these coveralls libraries don't work too well on AppVeyor.
Quick fix is to copy the AppVeyor branch env variable to one named the
same as Travis CI's.
Filled out changelog.
A better reset.

Fixed tests, changed version.

Forgot to run tests. Wasn't showing /all, /fg, or /bg before.

New CSBI method. atexit fix, better list_tags().

Previous GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo code worked everywhere except in
Python 2.7 x64. Trying a new way for 100% compatibility.

Improved list_tags() sorting.

_reset_colors() sets absolute colors instead of going through
_set_color(). Since the black background code is 0, which also indicates
the user is only setting the foreground color, _reset_colors() should
set the already-known fg and bg colors itself. Before it was not
resetting the background color.
Small tweaks.
Added WinXP comment.

Updated README/examples, added Windows auto colors

Tested out auto colors on Windows with all available backgrounds for
best user experience.

Updated screenshots.
Fixing example misprint.
Increased test coverage.

Removing isatty() check, context no atexit.

Checking for isatty() brings more problems than it solves.

When using Windows() as a context manager, there is no need to expose
reset_atexit since it always calls disable() in the end.
Making Windows.disable() safe.

Reverting travis, supporting detached.

In py3, out and err streams are _io and behave differently. Instead of
assuming that sys.__stdout__ and err are guaranteed to be valid, backing
up whatever used to be sys.stdout and err instead.

Travis OSX image does not currently support Python.
Trying easy_install pyyaml.
Retry x64.

Trying again with .git.

Instead of deleting .git directory, which breaks coveralls, moving it up
one directory and then back.

Fixing pytest skip, pip fix for Windows.

py3.4 still giving me problems on Windows. It apparently already removed
--no-clean even though the bug tracker stated they're un-deprecating it.

Removing the .git file during install for Windows CI. Hopefully that
fixes it on all versions of Python on Windows.

Auto background colors, simple Windows test.

Context manager has same arguments as static method.

Example shows off color stripping too.
Adding coveralls token.

Need to manually install pytest.

setup.py seems to fail to install pytest unless I run the test command
twice. Installing it manually.
Trying another way to download get-pip.py

Stupid mistake.

I forgot to change one line.
Trying another download command for windows.

Fixed missing pip and IndexError on cleanup.

pip not installed in 27 and 33 versions of Python in the AppVeyor
environment. Installing it myself.

On Windows doing `pip install .` raises an IndexError when trying to
delete the copied .git directory. Adding --no-clean seems to fix it in
my VM.
Adding OSX and Windows support.
Worked on docstrings.

Holy shit it works.

I think this is code complete. I just need to work on docstrings and the
README/screenshots.

Got all colors working. Color parity between Windows and Linux.

Resetting colors on disable. Optionally disable atexit.

Unlike linux/osx/unix, I have access to the current background color of
the user's terminal. Adding optional feature to automatically select
light or dark text to make it readable.

I can't believe I did this in 5 days working on this after work lol.

Started work on native Windows support.

Colorama was nice but it was a dependency. I'm trying to keep things
simple and straightforward. Plus it only supported dark colors.

Started working on Windows support for dark and light colors. Background
colors aren't yet fully implemented, neither are color resetting.

Update README.md

Travis is stuck, doing this insignificant change to kickstart it.
